A '''tranny chaser''' is term used by some to denote a person who loves or is attracted to [[transsexual]] or [[transgendered]] people.  It is usually applied to non-transgendered men who are attracted to pre or non-operative [[transwomen]].  Although in common usage, it is seen by many in the applicable group as offensive, with terms such as "admirer" being preferred instead.

== References in pop culture ==
* "[[Barry Zuckerkorn]]" ([[Henry Winkler]]), a lawyer on the television series '''[[Arrested Development]]''' has a penchant for transgendered prostitutes.
* "[[Matt McNamara]]" ([[John Hensley]]), a high school student on the television series '''[[Nip/Tuck]]''', learns that a former lover is transsexual and becomes fascinated with them.

